  <h2>Selected work</h2>

  <div class="entry">
    <h3>energia-forecast</h3>
    <p class="meta">2026 · personal project · in production</p>
    <p>
      A day-ahead forecasting system for Portuguese electricity demand and MIBEL market
      prices, running autonomously on free-tier infrastructure. Four public data sources
      ingested daily; LightGBM models evaluated with a leakage-free rolling-origin backtest
      (demand MAPE 2.8%, price P50 MAE 13.2 EUR/MWh, both beating their naive baselines);
      conformally calibrated P10-P90 intervals; every forecast stored immutably and scored
      in public against outcomes.
    </p>
    <p>
      Built end to end with AI-assisted development (Claude Code), with me as architect and
      reviewer; the design decisions are recorded as ADRs in the repository.
    </p>
